Key Match Events: Joel Embiid had 28 points and 12 rebounds, leading the Philadelphia 76ers to a 123-94 victory over the Brooklyn Nets.
Tyrese Maxey contributed significantly with 7 assists and an and-1 bucket.
Ziaire Williams was the top scorer for the Brooklyn Nets with 19 points.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was held at Barclays Center in Brooklyn, NY with an attendance of 17,926.
The Philadelphia 76ers now lead the regular season series 2-0 against the Brooklyn Nets.
